Niger Rebels End Fight in Northeast, Give Up Weapons, Sahel Says

-- B y   D j i b r i l   S a i d o u
-- 
2011-08-29T13:58:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/niger-rebels-end-fight-in-northeast-give-up-weapons-sahel-says.html
Fighters in  Niger’s  northeast region
of Tanout agreed to stop their battle against the West African
nation’s government, state-owned broadcaster Voix du Sahel
reported, citing Prime Minister Brigi Rafini.  About 130 of the rebels laid down their weapons and agreed
to support a national  peace process , the broadcaster cited
Rafini as saying after a meeting in Zinder, the country’s
second-biggest city.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Djibril Saidou in Niamey via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Emily Bowers  in Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net . 